# Yakisugi=20

In a project from Make: V97, Seattle woodwork Len Collum explains the Japan=
ese art of charring wood called _yakisugi_.  One of the typical uses is to =
make siding boards.=20

=E2=80=9C=E2=80=9CThe name yakisugi (=E7=84=BC=E6=9D=89) derives from two J=
apanese words: yaki (=E7=84=BC) meaning burned, charred, or broiled, and su=
gi (=E6=9D=89) referring to a Japanese cedar tree, Cryptomeria japonica.=E2=
=80=9C =E2=80=94 Len Collum

